  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "76",
      "note": "The term sakar (lit., \"wine\" or, generically, \"intoxicants\") is contrasted here with rizq hasan (\"wholesome sustenance\"), thus circumscribing both the positive and the negative properties and effects of alcohol. Although this surah was revealed about ten years before the Qur'anic prohibition of intoxicants in 5:90-91, there is no doubt that their moral condemnation is already implied in the above verse (Ibn 'Abbas, as quoted by Tabari; also Razi)."
    }
